¶ It's an Irish ¶

1204
01:23:26,469 --> 01:23:35,069
¶ Lullaby ¶¶

1205
01:23:58,109 --> 01:24:00,309
Sing "Roll out
the barrel."

1206
01:24:00,389 --> 01:24:01,989
Put a lid on it,
will you, Mom?

1207
01:24:02,069 --> 01:24:05,629
Don't take that tone of voice
with your mother. Show some respect.

1208
01:24:05,709 --> 01:24:08,669
Winston.

1209
01:24:08,750 --> 01:24:11,429
Why, thank you, Bernie.

1210
01:24:16,430 --> 01:24:18,269
Something funny?

1211
01:24:20,229 --> 01:24:22,629
Oh, we were just
telling "Davis" stories.

1212
01:24:22,669 --> 01:24:25,149
Oh, how fun!

1213
01:24:26,229 --> 01:24:28,549
Davis! Davis!

1214
01:24:28,630 --> 01:24:32,709
Do you remember that time you built that
tree house in my parent's backyard?

1215
01:24:32,789 --> 01:24:36,590
- It was so incredible.
- Davis built me a tree house.

1216
01:24:36,669 --> 01:24:38,149
He did?

1217
01:24:38,230 --> 01:24:40,669
Yes, on our
honeymoon night.

1218
01:24:40,749 --> 01:24:43,749
- Really? - Uh-hmm. In a big
tree up in the Boston Common.

1219
01:24:43,829 --> 01:24:47,869
The cops didn't stop you hammering away
in the middle of Boston Common?

1220
01:24:47,949 --> 01:24:49,949
Remember you used to play
a concertina?

1221
01:24:50,030 --> 01:24:51,869
Davis?

1222
01:24:51,950 --> 01:24:55,469
I prefabricated the panels and secured
it to the trees with cable suspension.

1223
01:24:55,510 --> 01:24:57,349
Isn't he the greatest?

1224
01:24:57,430 --> 01:24:59,749
What line of work
are you in, Bernie?

1225
01:24:59,829 --> 01:25:01,830
- I'm retired.
- Oh? From what?

1226
01:25:01,909 --> 01:25:05,429
From all the big,
hairy bullshit.

1227
01:25:07,749 --> 01:25:10,029
Davis, do you remember
our adventure walks?

1228
01:25:10,109 --> 01:25:13,429
- Huh? Oh, yeah.
- This one time...

1229
01:25:13,509 --> 01:25:15,270
we went lookin' for
a crashed meteor.

1230
01:25:15,349 --> 01:25:18,389
Son, could we
speak to you a second?

1231
01:25:18,469 --> 01:25:20,309
We've been
talking with Mary...

1232
01:25:20,389 --> 01:25:22,629
and she wants to get
back together with Bernie.

1233
01:25:22,709 --> 01:25:25,669
Your father and I were thinking,
if they could be close to Gwen...

1234
01:25:25,749 --> 01:25:27,629
- Like we're close to you.
- Right.

1235
01:25:27,669 --> 01:25:30,829
Well, I'll, I'll build them
a cottage across the pond.

1236
01:25:30,910 --> 01:25:35,389
Davis, did we or did we not adventure
walk from Manhattan to Boston?

1237
01:25:35,469 --> 01:25:37,429
- Yes, we did.
- Satisfied?

1238
01:25:37,509 --> 01:25:40,749
- I never said you didn't.
- Ha! Like hell!

1239
01:25:40,790 --> 01:25:42,909
Do you think,
for instance,

1240
01:25:42,989 --> 01:25:47,389
that this boy could have designed
a house as creative as this...

1241
01:25:47,469 --> 01:25:51,669
on a corporate,
kiss-ass committee?

1242
01:25:51,709 --> 01:25:56,069
All I said was that you and Davis
are well-suited for each other.

1243
01:25:56,150 --> 01:26:00,149
- I know what that means.
- I meant you're both creative.

1244
01:26:00,229 --> 01:26:03,589
In other words, we're both liars.
I hope you're hearing this.

1245
01:26:03,669 --> 01:26:06,549
- Sweetheart!
- Are you listening to what she's saying?

1246
01:26:06,629 --> 01:26:10,029
- I don't hear anything.
- That's exactly the problem.

1247
01:26:10,109 --> 01:26:12,629
You don't hear and
you don't see.

1248
01:26:12,709 --> 01:26:17,229
Don't you think I know
you're in love with my husband?

1249
01:26:17,309 --> 01:26:21,629
Do you think I don't know about your sympathy
for him for having a fruitcake like me?

1250
01:26:21,669 --> 01:26:25,469
You had your chance.
You had it building your tree house,

1251
01:26:25,549 --> 01:26:30,469
on adventure walks and on the day he
offered you this house, and you blew it.

1252
01:26:30,549 --> 01:26:32,630
I'm the one
who found him.

1253
01:26:32,709 --> 01:26:37,549
I'm the one who knows what he's worth
and you're the one he wants.

1254
01:26:44,150 --> 01:26:47,629
You're the one he wants,
goddamnit!

1255
01:26:54,949 --> 01:26:59,110
I, I'm sorry.
I, I better go after her.

1256
01:27:02,469 --> 01:27:06,549
- Davis!
- I'm sorry about this and about my father.

1257
01:27:06,629 --> 01:27:10,229
I remember Bernie.
He was always that way.

1258
01:27:10,309 --> 01:27:13,149
I don't know what's going on,
but keep this in mind.

1259
01:27:13,189 --> 01:27:17,750
I wouldn't have seen this house if it weren't
for that wife or giving you the promotion...

1260
01:27:17,829 --> 01:27:21,549
if I hadn't seen
this house.

1261
01:27:33,950 --> 01:27:36,550
You are the best.
It was miraculous!

1262
01:27:36,589 --> 01:27:39,029
I got the promotion.

1263
01:27:39,069 --> 01:27:41,750
- Can I have your handkerchief, please?
- What?

1264
01:27:41,829 --> 01:27:44,269
Oh, yeah, right.

1265
01:27:47,869 --> 01:27:51,589
It all looked so hopeless,
especially between Becky and your dad,

1266
01:27:51,669 --> 01:27:53,589
I mean, Ralph.

1267
01:27:53,669 --> 01:27:55,989
In one stroke,
you fixed everything.

1268
01:27:56,069 --> 01:28:01,069
Smashing the gifts was a bit over
the top but who am I to complain?

1269
01:28:01,149 --> 01:28:03,509
You did it, Gwen.
You did it!

1270
01:28:03,589 --> 01:28:07,109
- I want this marriage to work.
- What?

1271
01:28:07,189 --> 01:28:10,029
You heard me, damn it.
Was Maui nothing to you?

1272
01:28:10,109 --> 01:28:14,429
Or Boomer, the way we were able to work
that out? Okay, we had counseling.

1273
01:28:14,509 --> 01:28:16,870
I'm not saying
everything is perfect...

1274
01:28:16,949 --> 01:28:20,229
but I really think
this marriage is worth saving.

1275
01:28:20,310 --> 01:28:22,509
What marriage?

1276
01:28:27,909 --> 01:28:29,749
Gwen?

1277
01:28:30,909 --> 01:28:32,549
Gwen.

1278
01:28:34,469 --> 01:28:36,749
Would you mind taking me
into town, please?

1279
01:28:36,789 --> 01:28:39,429
- Sure.
- Thank you.

1280
01:28:39,469 --> 01:28:41,830
Gwen!

1281
01:28:44,629 --> 01:28:47,309
Gwen!

1282
01:29:17,230 --> 01:29:22,069
- She left me. She left me, Becky.
- Oh, Davis.

1283
01:29:22,109 --> 01:29:24,029
I don't know
what got into her.

1284
01:29:24,069 --> 01:29:27,349
I thought the relationship
was going fine. I, I really did.

1285
01:29:27,429 --> 01:29:29,909
You tried.
You did your best.

1286
01:29:29,949 --> 01:29:31,869
I was never
dishonest with her.

1287
01:29:31,949 --> 01:29:35,389
I always told her the truth
about you, everything.

1288
01:29:35,470 --> 01:29:37,670
Davis?

1289
01:29:37,749 --> 01:29:41,189
Was it true about the way
you met her in the hospital,

1290
01:29:41,230 --> 01:29:43,509
about the way
you got married,

1291
01:29:43,589 --> 01:29:46,149
the trip to Maui and
building that tree house?

1292
01:29:59,429 --> 01:30:01,869
Look at me,
I'm crying like an idiot.

1293
01:30:01,949 --> 01:30:04,149
Oh, of course
you're crying.

1294
01:30:04,189 --> 01:30:07,669
I mean, I'm really...
God, Becky!

1295
01:30:07,749 --> 01:30:10,069
Oh, Davis.

1296
01:30:10,149 --> 01:30:14,469
Just tell me the truth.

1297
01:30:21,150 --> 01:30:23,470
- Becky?
- Yes?

1298
01:30:23,509 --> 01:30:27,109
Everything she said
was true.

1299
01:30:34,389 --> 01:30:36,949
Gwen!
Gwen!

1300
01:30:36,989 --> 01:30:40,269
Gwen, Gwen!

1301
01:30:43,429 --> 01:30:46,229
I love you, Gwen.
I wanna marry you.

1302
01:30:46,309 --> 01:30:49,109
Is that it?

1303
01:30:49,149 --> 01:30:51,229
Well, yeah.

1304
01:30:54,149 --> 01:30:55,949
Look, Davis, we're not
right for each other.

1305
01:30:56,029 --> 01:30:58,789
- What?
- I can see that now.

1306
01:30:58,870 --> 01:31:01,309
I don't want you to feel bad
about any of this.

1307
01:31:01,389 --> 01:31:04,949
You were really kind of decent to me,
most of the time.

1308
01:31:05,030 --> 01:31:07,749
I can change, Gwen.
I can live in a make-believe world.

1309
01:31:07,829 --> 01:31:11,949
Hell, I already was. Half the things
we tell ourselves are fiction.

1310
01:31:12,030 --> 01:31:13,989
The only thing I know that's real
is that I love you.

1311
01:31:14,069 --> 01:31:16,349
I used to think
that was enough too.

1312
01:31:16,389 --> 01:31:20,549
- Isn't it?
- Step aboard, please.

1313
01:31:20,589 --> 01:31:22,349
Wait!

1314
01:31:22,389 --> 01:31:27,069
Don't you remember the time I had myself
delivered to you in a box for your birthday?

1315
01:31:27,110 --> 01:31:29,629
And how the guy I paid
screwed up...

1316
01:31:29,709 --> 01:31:31,949
and delivered me
to the wrong apartment?

1317
01:31:31,989 --> 01:31:35,269
And how the lady
who opened the box...

1318
01:31:35,309 --> 01:31:37,029
freaked out and
started screaming?

1319
01:31:37,109 --> 01:31:40,550
And I ran out just as you
poked your head into the hall.

1320
01:31:40,629 --> 01:31:44,709
The next thing I know, this one's
bashing me for having an affair...

1321
01:31:44,749 --> 01:31:47,069
and this one's bashing me
for being some kind of...

1322
01:31:47,150 --> 01:31:49,829
gift-wrapped pervert?

1323
01:31:49,909 --> 01:31:53,989
All I had to protect myself
was a dozen roses.

1324
01:31:54,069 --> 01:31:56,389
And you never even
read the note.

1325
01:31:57,749 --> 01:31:59,589
What did
the note say?

1326
01:31:59,669 --> 01:32:04,629
I'll tell you what it said.
It said...

1327
01:32:09,230 --> 01:32:11,550
Marry me, Gwen.
I'm lost without you.

1328
01:32:36,829 --> 01:32:38,669
What about my parents?

1329
01:33:23,710 --> 01:33:26,709
I love you, Gwen.

1330
01:33:26,789 --> 01:33:29,389
Actually, it's Jessica.

